          Authentication and Authorization :- 
              Authentication is the process of verifying the identity of a user,
              ensuring they are who they claim to be. Authorization occurs after authentication and determines what resources or actions the authenticated user is allowed to access. If authentication fails,
              the server typically returns a 401 Unauthorized error. If authentication succeeds but the user does not have permission,
              it returns a 403 Forbidden error.



            Authentication Example :-
                         Username & password login 
                         OTP verification 
                         Biometric login 
                         JWT token verification

